## Context
Research note originally specified 7 figures and 7 tables. Peer review simulation
(5-agent panel, 2026-04-13) recommended trimming to 8 display items total.
Scripts follow project convention: plot_* prefix, --output argument, Makefile rule.

## Main paper (4 tables + 4 figures)

Tables:
- T2: Four-quadrant classification (2x2, counts + mean cited_by)
- T4: Isolation scores by quadrant (summary stats + permutation test p-values)
- T6: Citation directionality (N->N, N->S, S->N, S->S + asymmetry ratio)
- T7: Temporal isolation trends (mean per quadrant x period + trend test)

Figures:
- F1+F2 merged: 2-panel UMAP scatter (left: by language, right: by quadrant)
- F3: Isolation score violins (one per quadrant, medians marked)
- F6: Temporal isolation lines (mean per quadrant across 3 periods)
- F5: Citation flow Sankey (only if H3 proxy is validated; otherwise cut)

## Supplementary (3 tables + 1 figure)
- T1: Language composition → sentence in text, full table in supplement
- T3: Language x cluster contingency (6x8, chi-squared) → supplement
- T5: Orphan TF-IDF terms by quadrant → supplement
- F7: Wordclouds → supplement (decorative)

## Cut entirely
- F4: Heatmap → redundant with T4
- F1 standalone → merged into 2-panel F1+F2

## Test
4 figure PNGs in content/figures/, 4 tables in content/tables/.

## Exit criteria
Figures and tables generated, committed, and visually reviewed by user.
